content.description: Dan 101 ledge is OFF. Bad feet; be careful not to place feet on the flaky rock underneath. Establish on deep square crack for left hand and slopper horn for right hand. Dyno straight up to ledge. Mantle to top. Feet will cut wide. Have a spotter. You can go for two smaller crimp ledges a few inches below the top.
content.location: In the cave there is a crack for left hand. Right hand is a slopper horn.

content.description: Start on Dan 101 ledge and mantle. Square crack underneath is good for left hand. Move left and mantle the same top as Gen Z.
content.location: Almost same start as Gen Z but Dan 101 ledge is on.

content.description: Start right and/or left hand on Dan 101 ledge, mantle the Dan ledge, go right, and mantle to top. Placement for pads here will most likely get wet. HAVE A SPOTTER.
content.location: Square crack is good for left hand. Dan 101 ledge is on.

content.description: The water is high, so if you climb Dan 101, your pad will likely get wet. There is a dry rock to place your pad on for Gen Z and Dan 102. HAVE A SPOTTER.
